article_title: South Dakota AG No-Shows Sentencing Hearing Where He Got No Jail Time After Killing a Man in Car Crash. The Victim’s Family Called Him ‘Cowardly.’
meta_description: South Dakota Attorney General Jason Ravnsborg (R) on Thursday pleaded no contest two of the three misdemeanor charges related to a deadly nighttime crash which killed a man east of Highmore, S.D., on September 12, 2020. Ravnsborg's ultimate punishment is a series of two $500 fines and about $3,700 in court costs. He will serve no jail time despite the underlying statute authorizing a potential of 30 days in jail for each two of the two offenses.
